The paper discusses the impact of journal choice on performance evaluations based on citation frequencies, which is a topic relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on publication venues and citation metrics, the most likely sub-categories are those related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and databases (cs.DB).
